Question: How to access keyvault secret from pod?
Create AKS cluster with enabled keyvault secrets provider, workload identity and oidc issuer
OIDC issuer URL is generated and secret store csi driver & secret store provider ds pods are running. user assigned MI is created. 
create new user assigned MI if required 
create keyvault and secret. assign access to secret to that user assigned MI either through RBAC or azure policy. 
create namespace & service account in that namespace. that service account will have label workload identity use as true and in annotations it will have client id of user assigned managed identity.
now this service account needs to be federated through Azure AD to access the managed identity.
create federated credentials through az identity federated-credentials command by passing, service account URL, OIDC URL & user assigned identity name. this will be reflected under user assigned managed identity -> settings -> federated credentials
create secret provider class for accessing azure keyvault secret
  provider: azure
  usePodIdentity: false - because we are not using pod identity for authentication
  useVMManagedIdentity: false - because we are not using the managed identity of VMSS that is attached to the nodes
  clientID: userassignedMI_client_id - because we r using workload identity by assigning federated creds to user assigned MI
  keyvaultName: 
  objects: secrets i want to retrieve from the keyvault
service account n secret providerclass has to be applied to the same namespace of application
create a deployment with the same serviceaccount, volumes & volumemounts 
 volume: 
  - name: secret-store-inline
    csi:
	  driver: secret-store.csi - crd name of csi driver
	  readOnly: true
	  volumeAttribute: 
		secretProviderClass: name of the secretProviderClass
secret from the keyvault is mounted to the pod at volumemount directory. it has created a file with the secret name and content as secret value. 

